{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The review input is scoped to the lines that changed, not the full content of each modified file.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Pass 1 dependency: local module handoff (diff parser -> review-input builder). The failure is at module boundaries: unchanged lines can leak when patch parsing and prompt assembly are wired together. No real OS/network/subprocess is required, and no real model judgment is required. Rejection gate: System/Agentic/Workflow rejected because behavior text is only about input scoping, not real HTTP/LLM quality/multi-agent steps.","test_description":"Run an in-process test that feeds real unified diffs plus full file contents through the actual parsing and input-construction modules, then assert the produced review payload contains only added/modified hunk lines and excludes unchanged context/out-of-diff lines.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.35,"Integration":0.58,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"Inline comments are attached to the correct positions in the diff view on the pull request.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Pass 1 dependency: real external API semantics (GitHub PR diff positioning). MOCK-HIDE applies: mocked clients can accept incorrect line/side/commit mapping that GitHub rejects or renders on wrong lines. Integration brake (a) is yes: needs real HTTP/API behavior, so System is minimum. Rejection gate: Agentic/Workflow rejected because correctness here is positional API mapping, not model quality or multi-agent reasoning.","test_description":"Against a real test PR on GitHub, post inline comments using the automation’s computed positions, then fetch PR review comments from GitHub and verify each comment lands on the expected file and diff line in the rendered PR context.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.17,"System":0.8,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The agent identifies at least one real defect in a pull request that contains a known introduced bug.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Pass 1 dependency: real model judgment quality (bug detection), which is non-deterministic and cannot be validated with deterministic stubs without hiding failures. LLM-DEP is yes. Rejection gate: Workflow rejected because this behavior requires a single agentic judgment outcome (find at least one real defect), not multiple agentic stages chained.","test_description":"Run the agent with the real model on a benchmark PR containing a seeded known bug and assert at least one posted finding correctly identifies that defect class/location; execute repeated trials with a pass-rate threshold to account for model variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.82,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Every finding listed in the top-level summary corresponds to an inline comment that was also posted — no findings appear in the summary without a matching inline comment.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Pass 1 dependency: consistency across local modules/state (finding tracker -> inline post results -> summary composer). Failure is cross-module data integrity, not OS/network semantics by itself. Integration brake: (a) no required real infra, (b) no required real model quality, (c) no multi-agent chain. Rejection gate: System rejected because behavior text is about correspondence invariant, which can be exposed with in-process wiring and mocked post responses.","test_description":"Execute the pipeline in-process with deterministic findings and a stubbed comment-poster returning posted comment metadata; assert every summary item has a matching inline-comment record and that orphan summary entries are impossible.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The full sequence — reading the diff, posting inline comments, posting the summary comment — completes correctly for a real pull request without manual intervention.","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Pass 1 dependency: full agent pipeline on real PR, combining agentic analysis plus external side effects in sequence. MULTI-STEP applies as a full agent pipeline end-to-end, so Workflow is minimum. Rejection gate: System rejected because behavior text explicitly requires the full sequence including the agent’s review step, not just API mechanics.","test_description":"Run the automation end-to-end on a real GitHub test PR with the real model enabled; verify unattended completion of all stages (diff read, inline comments posted, summary posted) and validate resulting artifacts on the PR.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.02,"System":0.17,"Agentic":0.09,"Workflow":0.72}}]}
